# v1 Adversarial Validation Package

This folder contains the compiled v1 validation report for retained update-asymmetry.

The report is not a new theory paper. It is an audit package summarizing:

- the protected internal-state formalism;
- the finite-grid adversarial benchmark;
- the direction-evidence audit;
- the classifier firewall;
- the v0.9-derived family validation table;
- the preliminary computational-mechanics proxy comparison;
- reproduction commands and current limitations.

The strongest current result is the adversarial finite-grid separation: TargetLossy produces 1024 / 3125 positive cells, while the matched controls produce zero internal-arrow positives.

The report should be read as a validation companion to the main paper in `paper/`.